Package: LARItools
Title: Lactylation-Associated Risk Index (LARI) for Pan-Cancer
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Zhihao", "Bo", , "bozhihao@tmu.edu.cn", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-6298-1953"))
Description: Computes the Lactylation-Associated Risk Index (LARI), a continuous
    prognostic metric derived from a pre-trained multi-omics Random Survival Forest
    (RSF) classifier integrating mRNA, lncRNA, and miRNA expression profiles. LARI
    quantifies the transcriptional activity of the lactylation-associated
    stromal-immune program at the individual sample level, with higher scores
    reflecting greater enrichment of extracellular matrix remodeling, immune
    suppression, and lactylation writer activity characteristic of the CS2 molecular
    subtype. The index has been validated as an independent prognostic indicator
    across eight external cohorts spanning six cancer types. Also provides
    LacCore Signature Scores via ssGSEA (GSVA >= 1.48 new API) and TIDE
    (Tumour Immune Dysfunction and Exclusion) scores via the Python tidepy
    package. Accepts gene expression matrices from RNA-seq or microarray
    platforms and returns per-sample scores suitable for survival analysis,
    risk stratification, and downstream multi-omics integration.
